    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-01-15T19:31:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-01-15T19:31:00-05:00" n="855"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d855">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">695A.00/1–1554: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d855fn1">This telegram was drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MRJG1">McClurkin</persName> and cleared with <persName
                            corresp="#p_DPS1">De Palma</persName>, <persName>Runyon</persName>,
                            <persName>Henry T. Smith</persName> (Deputy Director, Office of South
                        Asian Affairs), and <persName corresp="#p_BRE1">Bacon</persName>. It was
                        repeated to Munsan-ni as 202, Seoul as 599, and Tokyo as 1665 with
                        instructions to pass to <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-01-15T19:31:00-05:00"
                            >January 15, 1954—7:31 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>839. Your 1094;<note n="2" xml:id="d855fn2">Dated Jan. 12, <ref target="#pg_1718"
                            >p. 1718</ref>.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 829.<note n="3" xml:id="d855fn3">In
                        this telegram, Jan. 14, the Department of State informed the Embassy in New
                        Delhi that until it received a text of <persName corresp="#p_TLGKS1"
                            >Thimayya</persName>’s letter and <persName corresp="#p_HGJE1"
                            >Hull</persName>’s proposed reply, it was holding up its response to
                        telegram 1094 from Seoul. (695A.0024/1–1454)</note> Assume text <persName
                        corresp="#p_TLGKS1">Thimayya</persName>’s January 14 letter<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d855fn4">For text, see Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                            >Bulletin</hi>, Jan. 25, 1954, pp. 113–115.</note> available you.
                    Telegraphing separately through military channels text reply <persName
                        corresp="#p_HGJE1">General Hull</persName> authorized make.<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d855fn5">For text, see <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, pp.
                        115–116.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Main purposes our reply are make clear: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>Communist intransigence made it impossible <gloss target="#t_NNRC1"
                                >NNRC</gloss> fully accomplish mission and led to breakdown
                            explanations. Same cause prevented Political Conference from meeting.
                            Nevertheless, in our opinion <gloss target="#t_NNRC1">NNRC</gloss> will
                            be defaulting on its obligation under terms reference by returning
                            prisoners before expiration period custody and by failing declare their
                            release to civilian status.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>We can not accept prisoners on terms defined <persName
                                corresp="#p_TLGKS1">Thimayya</persName>’s letter implying we should
                            retain them in prisoner status until Political Conference meets and
                            considers their disposition.</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>If <gloss target="#t_CFI1">CFI</gloss> unilaterally return custody
                                <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss> 20 January <gloss
                                target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> would clearly not be justified using
                            force against them but from humanitarian considerations and to insure
                            them full enjoyment benefits Agreement <gloss target="#t_UNC1"
                                >UNC</gloss> would arrange for their accommodation and
                            disposition.</item>
                        <label>(4)</label>
                        <item>Return prior January 23 is failure by <gloss target="#t_NNRC1"
                                >NNRC</gloss> fully discharge its duties but this does not affect
                                <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss> right become civilians that
                            date and <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> in accordance Agreement on
                                <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POWs</gloss> will honor obligation treat
                            them as fully entitled freedom as civilians on January 23.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0610" n="1728" xml:id="pg_1728"/>
                <p>For your information we want avoid any implication we understand or could accept
                        <persName corresp="#p_TLGKS1">Thimayya</persName>’s letter as an
                    interpretation under paragraph 24 Terms of Reference.</p>
                <p>Time public release reply <persName corresp="#p_TLGKS1">Thimayya</persName>’s
                    letter will be determined Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
